SIMPLE: tonneau
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tonneau
<hw>Ton`neau"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>Tonneaux</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In France, a light-wheeled vehicle with square or rounded body and
rear entrance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Automobiles)</fld> <def>Orig., the after part of
the body with entrance at the rear (as in vehicle in def. 1); now, one
with sides closing in the seat or seats and entered by a door usually at
the side, also, the entire body of an automobile having such an after
part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>same as <er>Tonne</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tonnihood</ent>⟦br⟧
